<h1 id="retail-price-adjustments" sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="28">Retail price adjustments</h1>


<p sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="32">This procedure will walk through creating a commerce price adjustment. A price adjustment can set an item's sale price directly, or modify its base sale price or trade agreement sale price. This procedure uses the USRT demo data company.</p>
<ol sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Click Pricing and discount management.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="35">Click the Price adjustments tab.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Click New.
<ul sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="37">
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="37">From here you can create all of the most commonly used price and discount rules, including discounts, price adjustments, trade agreement journals, and category pricing rules.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="38">Click Price adjustment.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="40">Expand the Lines section.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="41">Click Add.
<ul sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">For this example, enter '81126' in the Product field. Then, enter '10.0' in the Discount percentage field.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">A discount percentage type price adjustment will reduce a base sales price or trade agreement sales price.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">Click Add.
<ul sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">For this example, enter '81125' in the Product field. Then, select 'Cash discount amount' in the Discount method field.    Finally, enter '5.0' in the Cash discount amount field.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="46">A Cash discount amount discount type is an amount taken off from a base price or a trade agreement price.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">Click Price groups.
<ul sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Select 'RP-Houston' in the Price group field.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="49">This will associate the Price adjustment to the Houston store.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">Click Save.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="51">Close the page.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">In the Status field, select 'Enabled'.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53">Click Save.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="54">Close the page.</li>
<li sourcefile="commerce/tasks/retail-price-adjustments.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">Refresh the page.</li>
</ol>
